<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p>3、List the titles of the print or digital publications, websites, journals, podcasts or other content with which you regularly engage.</p>
<p>4、List the movies, albums, shows, museums, lectures, events at your school or other entertainments that you enjoyed most during secondary/high school (in person or online).</p>
<p>5、Columbia students take an active role in improving their community, whether in their residence hall, classes or throughout New York City. Their actions, small or large, work to positively impact the lives of others. Share one contribution that you have made to your family, school, friend group or another community that surrounds you. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">6、Why are you interested in attending Columbia University? </p>
<p>7、For applicants to Columbia College, please tell us what from your current and past experiences (either academic or personal) attracts you specifically to the areas of study that you previously noted in the application. </p>
<p>8、For applicants to Columbia Engineering, please tell us what from your current and past experiences (either academic or personal) attracts you specifically to the areas of study that you previously noted in the application. （100字以内）</p>
<p><strong>6. University of Pennsylvania 宾夕法尼亚大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、How did you discover your intellectual and academic interests, and how will you explore them at the University of Pennsylvania? Please respond considering the specific undergraduate school you have selected. (300-450字)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、At Penn, learning and growth happen outside of the classroom, too. How will you explore the community at Penn? Consider how this community will help shape your perspective and identity, and how your identity and perspective will help shape this community. (150-200字)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>7. University of Chicago 芝加哥大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p3.itc.cn/images01/20200809/6c9cdcc8bdff4847bfe83c3ec91e4152.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>必选：</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">How does the University of Chicago, as you know it now, satisfy your desire for a particular kind of learning, community, and future? Please address with some specificity your own wishes and how they relate to UChicago.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>必选补充文书，七选一：</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Who does Sally sell her seashells to? How much wood can a woodchuck really chuck if a woodchuck could chuck wood? Pick a favorite tongue twister (either originally in English or translated from another language) and consider a resolution to its conundrum using the method of your choice. Math, philosophy, linguistics... it's all up to you (or your woodchuck).</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、What can actually be divided by zero?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、The seven liberal arts in antiquity consisted of the Quadrivium — astronomy, mathematics, geometry, and music — and the Trivium — rhetoric, grammar, and logic. Describe your own take on the Quadrivium or the Trivium. What do you think is essential for everyone to know?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4、Subway maps, evolutionary trees, Lewis diagrams. Each of these schematics tells the relationships and stories of their component parts. Reimagine a map, diagram, or chart. If your work is largely or exclusively visual, please include a cartographer's key of at least 300 words to help us best understand your creation.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">5、"Do you feel lucky? Well, do ya, punk?" - Eleanor Roosevelt. Misattribute a famous quote and explore the implications of doing so.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">6、Engineer George de Mestral got frustrated with burrs stuck to his dog’s fur and applied the same mechanic to create Velcro. Scientist Percy Lebaron Spencer found a melted chocolate bar in his magnetron lab and discovered microwave cooking. Dye-works owner Jean Baptiste Jolly found his tablecloth clean after a kerosene lamp was knocked over on it, consequently shaping the future of dry cleaning. Describe a creative or interesting solution, and then find the problem that it solves.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">7、In the spirit of adventurous inquiry (and with the encouragement of one of our current students!) choose one of our past prompts (or create a question of your own). Be original, creative, thought provoking. Draw on your best qualities as a writer, thinker, visionary, social critic, sage, citizen of the world, or future citizen of the University of Chicago; take a little risk, and have fun!</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>10. Duke University 杜克大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>必选：（200字内）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Please share with us why you consider Duke a good match for you. Is there something in particular about Duke’s academic or other offerings that attract you? </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>可选：（250字内）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Duke University seeks a talented, engaged student body that embodies the wide range of human experience; we believe that the diversity of our students makes our community stronger. If you’d like to share a perspective you bring or experiences you’ve had that would help us understand you better, perhaps a community you belong to or your family or cultural background, we encourage you to do so here. Real people are reading your application, and we want to do our best to understand and appreciate the real people applying to Duke. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Duke’s commitment to diversity and inclusion includes sexual orientation, gender identity, and gender expression. If you would like to share with us more about your identity, you can do so here, or use any previous essay prompt you feel is appropriate. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>11. Johns Hopkins University约翰霍普金斯大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/images01/20200809/7048295d947341f4b9a3dadad4ac735f.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Successful students at Johns Hopkins make the biggest impact by collaborating with others, including peers, mentors, and professors. Talk about a time, in or outside the classroom, when you worked with others and what you learned from the experience. (400字内)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>14.Brown University 布朗大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>三选一（250字内）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Brown’s Open Curriculum allows students to explore broadly while also diving deeply into their academic pursuits. Tell us about an academic interest (or interests) that excites you, and how you might use the Open Curriculum to pursue it. (250 words)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、At Brown, you will learn as much from your peers outside the classroom as in academic spaces. How will you contribute to the Brown community? (250 words)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、Tell us about a place or community you call home. How has it shaped your perspective? (250 words)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>17. Cornell University 康奈尔大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p8.itc.cn/images01/20200809/cb4ac09bc45a4503b1dcfecbfd2dad53.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>对应各自申请专业（650字内）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- College of Agriculture and Life Sciences: Why are you drawn to studying the major you have selected? </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- Please discuss how your interests and related experiences have influenced your choice. Specifically, how will an education from the College of Agriculture and Life Sciences (CALS) and Cornell University help you achieve your academic goals?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- College of Architecture, Art, and Planning: What is your "thing"? What energizes you or engages you so deeply that you lose track of time? Everyone has different passions, obsessions, quirks, inspirations. What are yours?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- College of Arts and Sciences: Students in Arts and Sciences embrace the opportunity to delve into multifaceted academic interests, embodying in 21st century terms Ezra Cornell’s “any person…any study” founding vision. Tell us about the areas of study you are excited to explore, and specifically why you wish to pursue them in our College.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- Cornell SC Johnson College of Business: What kind of a business student are you? The Cornell SC Johnson College of Business offers two distinct business programs, the Charles H. Dyson School of Applied Economics and Management and the School of Hotel Administration. Please describe how your interests and ambitions can be met through one or both of the Schools within the College.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- College of Engineering: Tell us about what excites you most about Cornell Engineering and/or studying engineering at Cornell University. How do you see yourself becoming a part of the Cornell Engineering community?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- College of Human Ecology: How has your decision to apply to the College of Human Ecology been influenced by your related experiences? How will your choice of major impact your goals and plans for the future?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- School of Industrial and Labor Relations: Using your personal, academic, or volunteer/work experiences, describe the topics or issues that you care about and why they are important to you. Your response should show us that your interests align with the ILR School.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>17. Rice University 莱斯大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">There is a breadth of intellectual opportunities here at Rice. Further explain your intended major and other areas of academic focus you may explore. （150字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>19. Washington University in St.Louis 华盛顿圣路易斯大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p8.itc.cn/images01/20200809/fd0d21aabe2043649d17922143dc3c36.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Tell us about something that really sparks your intellectual interest and curiosity and compels you to explore more in the program/area of study that you indicated. It could be an idea, book, project, cultural activity, work of art, start-up, music, movie, research, innovation, question, or other pursuit. （300字内）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>24. Georgetown University乔治城大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Indicate any special talents or skills you possess.（250字内）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Briefly discuss the significance to you of the school or summer activity in which you have been most involved. （半页纸，大约1000字符）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、As Georgetown is a diverse community, the Admissions Committee would like to know more about you in your own words. Please submit a brief essay, either personal or creative, which you feel best describes you. （一页纸）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4、What does it mean to you to be educated? How might Georgetown College help you achieve this aim? （单行，一页纸，科学与数学或语言学的申请人需要陈述他们所选的专业）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>25. University of Michigan，Ann Arbor 密歇根大学安娜堡分校</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p2.itc.cn/images01/20200809/0b5536f4bbb64212a281008f1baae5b5.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Everyone belongs to many different communities and/or groups defined by (among other things) shared geography, religion, ethnicity, income, cuisine, interest, race, ideology, or intellectual heritage. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Choose one of the communities to which you belong, and describe that community and your place within it. (必选，300字)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Describe the unique qualities that attract you to the specific undergraduate College or School (including preferred admission and dual degree programs) to which you are applying at the University of Michigan. How would that curriculum support your interests? (必选，550字)</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>27.Wake Forest University 维克森林大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、List five books you have read that intrigued you.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Tell us how a work of fiction you’ve read has helped you to understand the world’s complexity. （300字内）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、What piques your intellectual curiosity, and why? （150字内）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4、At Wake Forest, we gather our students in “Calls to Conversation,” congregating small groups around dinner tables in faculty’s and administrators’ homes to discuss topics organized around a theme, for example “arts for social change,” “gender in society,” and “leading a meaningful life.” If you could design a theme for a “Call to Conversation,” what would you choose, and why? （150字内）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">5、We live in an age intensely interested in heroes. Professor Joseph Campbell defined “hero” as “someone who has given his or her life to something bigger than oneself.” Describe a hero in public life and how and why, in your opinion, they meet Professor Campbell‘s definition.（150字内）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>28. University of Virginia 弗吉尼亚大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p7.itc.cn/images01/20200809/396d3e8c95e24c11a47ee6ddff78e18e.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>1、对应各自申请专业（半页纸，250字）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- College of Arts and Sciences - What work of art, music, science, mathematics, literature, or other media has surprised, unsettled, or inspired you, and in what way?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- School of Engineering and Applied Sciences - Describe an engineering feat that serves the common good and why it inspires you to study engineering.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- School of Architecture - Describe significant experience that deepened your interest in studying in the School of Architecture.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">- School of Nursing - Describe a health care-related experience or another significant interaction that deepened your interest in studying nursing.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"> - Kinesiology Program - Discuss experiences that led you to apply to the kinesiology major. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>2、五选一（半页纸，250字）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（1） What’s your favorite word and why?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（2） We are a community with quirks, both in language and in traditions. Describe one of your quirks and why it is part of who you are.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（3） Student self-governance, which encourages student investment and initiative, is a hallmark of the UVA culture. In her fourth year at UVA, Laura Nelson was inspired to create Flash Seminars, one-time classes which facilitate high-energy discussion about thought-provoking topics outside of traditional coursework. If you created a Flash Seminar, what idea would you explore and why?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（4） UVA students paint messages on Beta Bridge when they want to share information with our community. What would you paint on Beta Bridge and why is this your message?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（5） Rita Dove, UVA English professor and former U.S. Poet Laureate, once said in an interview that "...there are times in life when, instead of complaining, you do something about your complaints." Describe a time when, instead of complaining, you took action for the greater good.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>29. Tufts University 塔夫茨大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Which aspects of the Tufts undergraduate experience prompt your application? In short, ‘Why Tufts?’（100-150字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、三选一（200-250字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（1）From recognizing break dancing as a new Olympic sport, to representation in media, to issues of accessibility in our public transit systems, what is something that you can talk about endlessly? What do you care about and why?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（2）Whether you’ve built circuit boards or written slam poetry, created a community event or designed mixed media installations, tell us: What have you designed, invented, engineered, or produced? Or what do you hope to?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（3）We all have a story to tell. And with over 5,000 undergraduate students on our campus, that is over 5,000 stories to share and learn. What’s yours?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>29. University of North Carolina-Chapel Hill 北卡大学教堂山分校</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p9.itc.cn/images01/20200809/799467ef2bd94d4f87a0f8136f9a7b8e.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>四选二（200-250字）：</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Tell us about a peer who has made a difference in your life.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、What do you hope will change about the place where you live?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、What is one thing that we don’t know about you that you want us to know?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4、What about your background, or what perspective, belief, or experience, will help you contribute to the education of your classmates at UNC?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>37. Boston College 波士顿学院</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>HCE专业写5，其他专业1-4任选一。（400字内）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Great art evokes a sense of wonder. It nourishes the mind and spirit. Is there a particular song, poem, speech, or novel from which you have drawn insight or inspiration?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、When you choose a college, you will join a new community of people who have different backgrounds, experiences, and stories. What is it about your background, your experiences, or your story, that will enrich Boston College’s community?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、Boston College strives to provide an undergraduate learning experience emphasizing the liberal arts, quality teaching, personal formation, and engagement of critical issues. If you had the opportunity to create your own college course, what enduring question or contemporary problem would you address and why?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4、Jesuit education considers the liberal arts a pathway to intellectual growth and character formation. What beliefs and values inform your decisions and actions today, and how will Boston College assist you in becoming a person who thinks and acts for the common good?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">5、For Human-Centered Engineering major applicants only: One goal of a Jesuit education is to prepare students to serve the Common Good. Human-Centered Engineering at Boston College strives to develop people who will integrate technical knowledge, creativity, and a humanistic perspective to address societal challenges and opportunities. How would a Boston College engineering education enable you to contribute towards these goals?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>46.University of Wisconsin Madison 威斯康辛麦迪逊大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p6.itc.cn/images01/20200809/d9c1e76241cb4b88b06dc94b7a3053e1.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Tell us why you would like to attend the University of Wisconsin–Madison. In addition, please include why you are interested in studying the major(s) you have selected. If you selected undecided, please describe your areas of possible academic interest.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>46.Villanova University 维纳诺瓦大学</strong>诺瓦大学</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>1、四选一，（250字）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（1）What is the truest thing that you know? How did you come to this conclusion?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（2）Villanovans are known for "holding doors open" because inclusion is at the core of who we are. Take us on a journey through your background and describe how your life experience has shaped your understanding of the word "inclusion".</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（3）Generation Z is arguably the most technologically savvy cohort in history. They find answers to questions, discover troves of new music, or even start the next global social movement, all within seconds. How has this seemingly limitless connectivity influenced the person you have become?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">（4）In St. Augustine's book Confessions, one of the themes is the idea of redemption and second chances. Tell us a story about second chances. It can be your experience or one that you have come across through others or through media.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、 Why do you want to call Villanova your new home and become part of our community? （100字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>48.University of Texas at Austin 德克萨斯大学奥斯汀分校</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>必选（250-300字，不超过40行）：</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Why are you interested in the major you indicated as your first-choice major?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Leadership can be demonstrated in many ways. Please share how you have demonstrated leadership in either your school, job, community, and/or within your family responsibilities.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、Please share how you believe your experiences, perspectives, and/or talents have shaped your ability to contribute to and enrich the learning environment at UT Austin, both in and out of the classroom.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>可选（250-300字，不超过40行）：</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Please share background on events or special circumstances that may have impacted your high school academic performance.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>50. University of Georgia 佐治亚大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>补充文书，必选（200–300字）：</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">The college admissions process can create anxiety. In an attempt to make it less stressful, please tell us an interesting or amusing story about yourself from your high school years that you have not already shared in your application.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>54. Syracuse University 雪城大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p7.itc.cn/images01/20200809/dedd16605bed4faaaa79b4691111b35a.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Who or what influenced you to apply to Syracuse University? （250字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Who is the person you dream of becoming and how do you believe Syracuse University can help you achieve this? （250字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>62.University of Washington 华盛顿大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">必选（500字内）：</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Tell a story from your life, describing an experience that either demonstrates your character or helped to shape it.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">必选（300字内）：</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Our families and communities often define us and our individual worlds. Community might refer to your cultural group, extended family, religious group, neighborhood or school, sports team or club, co-workers, etc. Describe the world you come from and how you, as a product of it, might add to the diversity of the UW.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">可选，个人其他补充信息（200字）：</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">You are not required to write anything in this section, but you may include additional information if something has particular significance to you. For example, you may use this space if:</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1. You have experienced personal hardships in attaining your education</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2. Your activities have been limited because of work or family obligations</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3. You have experienced unusual limitations or opportunities unique to the schools you attended</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>64. University of Massachusetts Amherst 马赛诸塞州阿姆赫斯特大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/images01/20200809/d3130de8b3204be293bf8d7cb23ab5bc.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Please tell us why you want to attend UMass Amherst（100字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Please tell us why you chose the major you did（100字）</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>104.University of Colorado Boulder 科罗拉多波尔德大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">补充文书，必选（250–650字）：</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">We value difference and support equity and inclusion of all students and their many intersecting identities. Pick one of your unique identities and describe its significance.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>University of Vermont 佛蒙特大学</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>五选一：</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、Why UVM?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Established in 1978 in a renovated gas station in Burlington, VT, Ben and Jerry’s is synonymous with the ice cream business. The company’s success and unique brand identity are due in part to their one-of-a-kind flavors. Which Ben &amp; Jerry’s ice cream flavor (real or imagined) best describes you?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">3、Whether they are constructing a robot, a stronger sense of community or an identity, UVM students are builders. What would you like to build?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">4、At UVM, learning extends far beyond the walls of our classrooms. From student-led organizations, to internships and study abroad experiences, UVM students are encouraged to pursue knowledge in all environments. Describe a time when you’ve learned in a non-traditional setting.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">5、Communities and organizations are stronger when they value diversity of thought. How do you create meaningful connections or conversations with others when they express opinions that differ from your own?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Babson College 巴布森学院</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p3.itc.cn/images01/20200809/61280373af854affb731c30f7ed865e8.png" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>一篇500字Essay或一分钟视频</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Your moment has arrived. Share with us the moments or experiences that have led you to apply to Babson College.</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>Trinity College 三一学院</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify"><strong>二选一（250字-600字间）</strong></p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">1、We live in an urban-global age with more than half of the planet’s people living in cities. </p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">Trinity College is an urban liberal arts college deeply engaged with the local community and committed to making an impact across the world. How do you aspire to use your education to impact local and global communities?</p>
<p class="ql-align-justify">2、Our mission states: “Engage. Connect. Transform. As the preeminent liberal arts college in an urban setting, Trinity College prepares students to be bold, independent thinkers who lead transformative lives.” Keeping the three pillars of the mission in mind, how do you see yourself contributing to the Trinity community?</p>
➜段落分析| 两个大类八个子类的形式与作用
http://www.sohu.com/a/412224294_490529	20409
<p>段落是论文的基石，是承载正式内容和非正式内容的最小单元。合理的分段既可以连贯地串联起不同意义的内容，也能让整体逻辑更严密。</p>
<p class="ql-align-right">文/学位与写作</p>
<p class="ql-align-right">转/Meeloun论文网</p>
<p>控制段落的长度（尽量不超过半页），给每一段落只分配一个主题和一个论点，让各种类型的段落交替出现，会让文章有波浪感，读者在阅读时能找到合理的节奏，有助于读者提高阅读兴趣。</p>
<p>段落表面上多种多样，实际上可以分成两大类，分别是<strong>无编码段落</strong>和<strong>编码段落</strong>。每一大类又包含4个子类。本文分析了不同类型段落的基本形式和作用。</p>
<p>我们将看到，<strong>可以通过强制添加论点来组织看上去松散的段落，可以通过强制添加编码来突出重要的段落</strong>。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p5.itc.cn/images01/20200809/1fec1b1eb843494d9485c1e528007507.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>A. 无编码段落的四种类型</strong></p>
<p>无编码段落是不带编号的段落。无编码段落包含两类，第一类是不含论点的段落或隐含论点的段落，第二类是含论点的段落。</p>
<p>举例而言，导航段落就是一种用于组织内容的不含论点的段落。它就像节目的主持人一样，可以组织和播报那些正式节目。在章节起始部分交代本节安排时，在中间有大块内容意思发生转折时，往往会使用导航段落。</p>
<p>致谢段落是隐含论点的段落，暗示要感谢谁。</p>
<p>比较重要的段落是带有主题和论点的段落，简称<strong>主题段落</strong>（topical sentence）。由于主题段落突出了一个完整的主题和论点，因此容易聚焦一条条核心内容，让读者抓住一个个要点，而不会混淆各种论点。</p>
<p>主题段落可以分为论点优先段落、背景优先段落、分析型段落和强制带论点的段落四种情形。</p>            <div class="lookall-box">
<div class="lookall-shadow"></div>
<section class="lookall">
<a href="javascript:;" class="show-all" id="showMore">
<em>展开全文</em>
</a>
</section>
</div>
<div class="hidden-content control-hide">
<p><strong>1.</strong> <strong>论点优先段落</strong></p>
<p>论点优先段落是这样一个段落单元，它拥有两部分，第一部分是<strong>论题语句</strong>（topical sentence），用于指出主题（topic）和论点（controlling idea）。第二部分是支持论点的内容。</p>
<p>论点优先是一种开门见山的做法，它有几个显而易见的用处：它声明了论点，它概括了一个段落的内容，它让读者一瞥要处理的主题，它暗示在给定的段落中如何讨论主题，它提示了过渡。 </p>
<p><strong>论点优先段落的五种类型</strong></p>
<p>（举例中，<strong>蓝色</strong> 字体为论题语句）</p>
<p><strong>a 分类型(classification)：</strong>把主要信息分成更小的类别。</p>
<p><strong>知识可以分为两种基本类型</strong>。第一种是显性知识，是那些媒介可以记载、可以传承和可以通过课堂、书本传授的知识。第二种是是隐性知识，是隐含在人们头脑中的知识，是人们头脑中掌握的经验、技能和想法等。</p>
<p><strong>b.故事型(narration,chronological)：</strong>按故事出现的时间顺序描述事件。</p>
<p><strong>他在研究生阶段，按期通过了各培养环节</strong>。入学后前两年，他以优异成绩完成了各门课程学习。第三年开始，他顺利通过资格考试并开始深入课题研究。在距毕业前一年，他完成了选题报告且发表了一篇学术论文。第五年，他的学位论文工作达到了毕业要求，以优异成绩通过博士论文答辩并取得博士学位。 </p>
<p><strong>c.证据与说明型</strong>(evidence and illustration)：用例子支持主题和论点。</p>
<p><strong>对于某些工科专业，学历越高，性别失衡现象越不严重</strong>。举例而言，XXX专业的本科生男女比例是9:1，硕士生比例是5:1，博士生则是5:3。可见，本科生男女比例是博士生男女比例的5.4倍。</p>
<p><strong>d.对比和比较型</strong>（contrast and comparison）：用于展示两个或更多事物之间的相似或不同。</p>
<p><strong>东西半球的平均气温的差异没有南北半球的平均气温的差异大</strong>。图n显示了全球不同地区的年平均气温。可见，南北半球的年平均气温分别为X和Y，差异为Z。而东西半球的年平均气温分别为x和y，差异为z。于是，南北半球年平均气温的差异是东西半球年平均气温差异的Z/z倍。</p>
<p><strong>e.因果关系型</strong>(cause and effect)：用于解释一个现象的原因。</p>
<p><strong>一年下来，南半球的地表面吸收的太阳热量比北半球的多</strong>。这源于地球的南北轴并不与地球绕太阳的轨道平面垂直，而是有一个倾斜。如图n所示，这一倾斜使得阳光更直接地指向南半球的垂直方向，这意味着较少的热量在到达地球南半球表面之前被大气吸收。北半球则与此不同，阳光到达地表面之前需要穿越较长距离的大气层。</p>
<p>论点优先的一种变体是写好论点优先段落后，把论题语句移动到段落的最后。此时，论题语句看上去是在下结论。</p>
<p><strong>2.</strong> <strong>背景优先段落</strong></p>
<p>背景优先段落包含三部分，分别是背景或来龙去脉、内容和结论，简称为C-C-C结构，这里的三个C，按顺序分别指Context, Content和Conclusion，即背景、内容和结论。这是门斯(Brett Mensh)和科尔丁(Konrad Kording)关于如何写好结构化论文的建议。</p>
<p>在这种背景优先的段落结构中，将描述简单分为开始、中间和结尾三部分，要求有一个清晰可辨的开头、一个意义明确的主体部分和一个结尾。开头交代背景或来龙去脉，中间介绍主体内容，最后将故事一步步推进到给出结论的结尾。</p>
<p>一开始就交代背景或缘由，可以让读者理解“为什么告诉我这个?”在结尾给出结论，可以让读者记住要点。中间放入的内容让读者思考，看到你的论点由背景到结论会有根有据。</p>
<p>这种“背景优先”的模式不同于“内容优先”的结构，“内容优先”的结构可能会让读者错过对“为什么告诉我这个”的交代。基于这些原因，门斯和科尔丁提倡将C-C-C作为“默认”的科学论文结构。</p>
<p><strong>3. 分析型段落</strong></p>
<p>一些特别大的论点需要举证和分析，此时可采用包含举证和分析的分析型段落。分析型段落的标准形式是TRIAC段落。该类段落按顺序出现如下几部分内容：</p>
<p>TRIAC即为Topic Sentence、Restatement、Illustration、Analysis和Conclusion的首写字母组合。</p>
<p>如果TRIAC段落太长，可以分成用关联词汇粘合的几个子段落。这从排版上看似乎是几个段落，但意义上只是一个段落。</p>
<p>例如，把论题语句和重述或限制组成一段，在结尾处声明“下面给出举证”（或达到同样效果的更符合语境的短语），以便将上下两个子段落关联到一起。把举证和分析组成排版上的第二段，把结论作为排版上的第三段。对于第三段，应使用恰当的过渡词（如“综上所述”）来提示下结论了，以便与上面的子段落关联起来。</p>
<p><strong>4. 强制带论点的段落</strong></p>
<p>有的内容本身就有主题和论点，自然使用主题段落。也有的看似松散，此时建议构建一个主题和论点，将其变为主题段落，以增加段落的意义。</p>
<p>例如，假设你在介绍一种仪器的参数，你可以在前面加上论题语句"<strong>XXX仪器涉及n种参数</strong>"来表示主题和论点，接下来交代每一种参数。以这种方式构建的段落就变成了属于证据与说明型的主题段落，比不添加论题语句的情形更利于阅读。</p>
<p>又如，你针对某一问题介绍了几篇参考文献，你在前面加上一句“<strong>一些作者研究了XXX问题</strong>”来表示主题和论点。接下来就可以一篇篇介绍具体的参考文献。</p>
<p>无编码段落就像大海中的一座座孤岛，需要通过语境 来理解 上下文联系</p>
<p>编码段落像网状结构中的一个个节点，可通过编号引用来构建协同关系</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p2.itc.cn/images01/20200809/48e5dd39baca4f1a9087bbd59c43885c.jpeg" max-width="600" /></p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><strong>B. 编码段落的四种类型</strong></p>
<p>编码段落是那些通过编码的引用与论文其它段落甚至很遥远的段落显式地规定了关联关系的段落。编码段落特别适合那些论点需要多个段落甚至多个章节才能说清楚的情形。正式数学段落、强制编码段落、题注段落就是这种编码段落。除此之外，参考文献等条目列表也属于编码段落。</p>
<p><strong>1.</strong> <strong>正式数学段落</strong></p>
<p>一般情况下，标准的数学论文包含一系列正式数学段落和一些非正式段落。正式数学段落有定义(Definition)、假设(Assumption)、引理(Lemma)、定理(Theorem)、推论(Corollary)、举例(Example)和证明(Proof)等形式。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p4.itc.cn/images01/20200809/1a2bf5a548f44459b32ea6b027b92411.jpeg" max-width="600"><span class="img-desc" style="font-size: 16px;">图1 数学段落（引理、定理、证明、举例）示例（Wu,1996,SINUM，33，1336）</span></img></p>
<p><strong>正式数学段落有几个特点</strong>：使用极为规范且言简意赅的逻辑语言，夹带数学符号和数学公式，拥有可用于交叉引用的标签和编号（如<strong>图1</strong>中的定理3.4），可能要求使用不同的字体（如意大利体）。</p>
<p><strong>不同的正式数学段落之间需要遵循一定的组织原则，通过编号交叉引用组成整体逻辑结构</strong>。除此之外，还需要有一些非正式或辅助段落用于铺垫、组织和点缀。这些非正式数学段落可以参照前面的无编码段落书写，用于描述动机、类比、例子和数学解释等。正式段落和非正式段落并行地出现，可以使读者能够从逻辑和认知两方面理解。</p>
<p><strong>最重要的数学结果一般放在定理之中</strong>。引理用于证明一个数学定理时引用，因此连同定理需要的定义和假设，放在定理之前。由定理可以引出可用于更具体情况的推论。</p>
<p>Reiter（1995）指出：数学段落必须符合线性顺序，即由简单到复杂的顺序。对于这种线性结构，引理的复杂程度越来越高，一个接一个，直到一个定理被证明，随后是一系列越来越复杂的推论。任何断言都应该从它所依赖的引理和定理得出。以引理作为基础、定理作为核心结果、推论作为收尾工作，帮助读者欣赏和快速浏览哪些是关键的想法。</p>
<p><strong>证明是确认结果的推理</strong>，要求可验证。无论引理、定理还是推论都需要证明。证明过程可能包含大量的数学符号与公式，交叉引用前面的引理或定理。一般情况下，一个证明包含许多小的段落，因此可以认为是一个组合段落。在证明的结尾处给终止符。如果不同的证明需要用到相同的论点，那么该论点就需要放在前面的一个引理之中，在证明中引用即可。</p>
<p><strong>2. 强制编码段落</strong></p>
<p>对于需要突出的结论、概念、法则等，可以将其变为强制编码段落。强制编码段落与数学段落类似，可以出现在非数学类论文中。以下内容可以形成强制编码段落（latex 排版软件可以自动生成）：</p>
<p>强制添加编码后，可以在全文其它地方对这些内容进行引用。例如，以下段落可以在其它地方引用：</p>
<p><strong>条件2.2</strong> 样本数量为20，其中，前10个样本在冷冻条件下制备，后10种在室温条件下制备。</p>
<p>需要注意的是，只在必要情况，对于比较重要的东西，才能使用强制编码段落，不能滥用。</p>
<p><strong>3. 题注段落</strong></p>
<p>图形和表格的题注都是编码段落。以图形题注为例，它是图形下方（个别期刊是上方）对图形或者包含子图的图形的注释，带有编号（如<strong>图2</strong>图形下方的题注带有编码Figure3）。</p>
<p class="ql-align-center"><img src="http://p1.itc.cn/images01/20200809/9db26926b1d14a93af26271579594a09.jpeg" max-width="600"><span class="img-desc" style="font-size: 16px;">图2 题注段落（Feng et al, Langmuir 2007, 23, 4892）</span></img></p>
<p>不同期刊对题注的详尽程度有不同的要求。一些期刊要求单凭看题注就能完全理解图的内容，此时题注可以有半页长度。也有一些期刊要求题注就像一个标题那么短，更多描述应放在正文中。</p>
<p>图形题注一般要给出图形的标题，指出是什么图形。除此之外，给出得到图形的必要条件，对图形中的一些必要元素进行描述。有子图时对子图进行描述。</p>
<p>图形本身、题注和图形描述是图形的三个要素。题注段落与图形组成整体，对图形的描述则放在正文中。</p>
<p>在正文中的图形描述与图形本身及其题注形成呼应。对于比较重要的图形描述，可以分成四个主题段落。第一段是引用图形并介绍得到图形的条件。第二段用于介绍图形的特征和趋势。第三段用于介绍特征与趋势的解释。第四段用于指出特征与趋势的含义。</p>
<p>例如，对于第一段，可以构建“<strong>图n给出了在...参数范围的...</strong>”作为论题语句，接下来是对该论题的说明（介绍一下横坐标是什么，纵坐标是什么，是在什么条件下得到该图的）。</p>
<p>又如，对于第二段，可以构建“<strong>从图n我们观察到几个有趣的特征</strong>”或相似语句作为论题语句，接下来指出具体的特征。</p>
<p>表格题注和描述也有相似要求。</p>
<p><strong>4. 条目段落</strong></p>
<p>参考文献列表、练习题等属于条目列表。脚注和尾注也采用条目形式。</p>
<p>需要指出的是，有的参考文献列表采取顺序编码制，有的则采取作者出版年制。对于后者，用作者和出版年表示编码，引用时引用作者和出版年。</p>
<p><strong>顺序编码制</strong>： 参考文献列表中的文献按正文引用文献的前后顺序排序，且每篇参考文献都有一个放在中括号中的编码，引用时以上标形式引用带中括号的编号。以引用序号为3的文献为例，可以使用句型“Dowell等人介绍了疫苗研究的发展历史[3]”或“疫苗研究具有悠久的历史[3]”来引用。</p>
<p><strong>作者出版年制</strong>：在参考文献列表中，按作者姓名的字母顺序排序，作者完全相同的几篇文献按出版年排序， 引用文献时，需要指出作者和出版年。以Dowell等人发表于2013年的文章为例（作者名为虚构），可以使用句型“Dowell等人（2013）介绍了疫苗研究的发展历史”或“疫苗研究具有悠久的历史（Dowell et al 2013）”来引用。</p>
